<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-02-17</DATELINE><TITLE>Coronaviruses: a paradigm of new emerging zoonotic diseases</TITLE><BODY>A novel type of coronavirus (2019-nCoV) infecting humans appeared in Wuhan, China, at the end of December 2019. Since the identification of the outbreak the infection quickly spread involving in one month more than 31,000 confirmed cases with 638 death. Molecular analysis suggest that 2019-nCoV could be originated from bats after passaging in intermediate hosts, highlighting the high zoonotic potential of coronaviruses.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>